  "prompt": "My neet rank is 8050,I belong to UR category,is there any chance of getting a government college under 15\u2105 quota? I have Madhya Pradesh domicile.",
  "response": "Your NEET rank of 8050 under the UR (Unreserved) category and Madhya Pradesh domicile puts you in a decent position to secure a seat in a government medical college under the 15% All India Quota (AIQ). However, the final outcome depends on several factors:\n\n### Factors to Consider:\n1. **Previous Year Cutoffs**: Analyze the previous year's cutoff ranks for government colleges under the 15% AIQ. These can give you a rough idea of your chances.\n2. **Seat Availability**: The number of seats available under the 15% AIQ can vary each year.\n3. **State Reservation Policies**: Your domicile in Madhya Pradesh may not directly impact the 15% AIQ, as it is a national quota, but it could help in state quota counseling.\n4. **Competition**: The competition can vary depending on the number of applicants and their ranks.\n\n### Based on Past Trends:\n- For the 15% AIQ, ranks below 10,000 have a good chance of securing a seat in government medical colleges, though the specific college may vary.\n- With a rank of 8050, you are likely to get a seat, but it might not be in the most prestigious colleges. \n\n### What You Can Do:\n1. **Participate in AIQ Counseling**: Ensure you register for the AIQ counseling process conducted by the Medical Counseling Committee (MCC).\n2. **State Quota Counseling**: Even if you don\u2019t secure a seat under the 15% AIQ, you have a strong chance in the state quota counseling for Madhya Pradesh, where your rank is quite competitive.\n\n### Conclusion:\nYes, there is a reasonable chance of securing a seat in a government medical college under the 15% AIQ with your rank. Stay updated with the counseling schedules and keep your options flexible to maximize your chances. Good luck!",
